{
  "doc_id": "32198",
  "text": "Ureide concentration in xylem sap. The ureide concentration in xylem was carried out with cuts in the plant stem in the height of 3 cm up of the root collar, at 9:00 h, in which the xylem sap was harvested during the period of 60 min. After the xylem sap was stored at -20°C until the extraction moment. The extraction was carried out with solution contained xylem sap, ultra pure water and NaOH at 0.5M in the proportion of 1:149:50 (v/v). Subsequently this solution was incubated for 8 min at 100°C and was promoted with the thermal shock for 5 min at 2°C. The ureide-N concentration was determined at 535 nm in agreement with the colorimetric method described by [CITATION_1] , in which alantoine was used as standard (Sigma chemicals).",
